  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Greeting'
      title: Greeting
      number: 1
      content: '    The elder to the beloved Gaius, whom I love in truth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Beloved, I pray that all may go well with you and that you may be
        in good health, as it goes well with your soul. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'For I rejoiced greatly when the brothers[[COMMENT(0)]] came and testified
        to your truth, as indeed you are walking in the truth. '
      comments:
      - number: '3 '
        content: "Or . In New Testament usage, depending on the context, the plural
          Greek word (translated \u201Cbrothers\u201D) may refer either to or to
          ; also verses 5, 10"
    - name: '4: Support and Opposition'
      title: Support and Opposition
      number: 4
      content: 'I have no greater joy than to hear that my children are walking in
        the truth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Beloved, it is a faithful thing you do in all your efforts for these
        brothers, strangers as they are, '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'who testified to your love before the church. You will do well to
        send them on their journey in a manner worthy of God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'For they have gone out for the sake of the name, accepting nothing
        from the Gentiles. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Therefore we ought to support people like these, that we may be fellow
        workers for the truth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'I have written something to the church, but Diotrephes, who likes
        to put himself first, does not acknowledge our authority. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'So if I come, I will bring up what he is doing, talking wicked nonsense
        against us. And not content with that, he refuses to welcome the brothers,
        and also stops those who want to and puts them out of the church.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Beloved, do not imitate evil but imitate good. Whoever does good
        is from God; whoever does evil has not seen God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: Final Greetings'
      title: Final Greetings
      number: 12
      content: 'Demetrius has received a good testimony from everyone, and from the
        truth itself. We also add our testimony, and you know that our testimony
        is true.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: '  I had much to write to you, but I would rather not write with pen
        and ink. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'I hope to see you soon, and we will talk face to face.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: Peace be to you. The friends greet you. Greet the friends, each by
        name.
      comments: []
